  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6049",
  "title": "`indexId` missing in `AutocompleteRenderState` type while being listed in the docs",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nThe [documentation for autocomplete](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/autocomplete/js/#connector-param-render-rendering-options) shows the `indices` containing a property named `indexId`, but this isn't reflected in the `AutocompleteRenderState` type [here](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/src/connectors/autocomplete/connectAutocomplete.ts#L38). This means that we can't index on the `indexId` without writing some smelly typescript.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nProviding steps to repro this type mismatch seems a bit excessive. However, I'm happy to do it if the above description isn't sufficient.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nSee comment above\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the `AutocompleteRenderState` type in [this file](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/master/packages/instantsearch.js/src/connectors/autocomplete/connectAutocomplete.ts#L38) to contain the `indexId` like described in the [docs](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/autocomplete/js/#connector-param-render-rendering-options).\n\n### Package version\n\ninstantsearch.js 4.64.3\n\n### Operating system\n\nmacOS 14.2.1\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
